
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-morin-bess-mvpn-fast-failover-02.txt'>
    <title>"Multicast VPN fast upstream failover", Thomas Morin, Robert Kebler</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-morin-bess-mvpn-fast-failover-02.txt</link>
    <description>This document defines multicast VPN extensions and procedures that allow fast failover for upstream failures, by allowing downstream PEs to take into account the status of Provider-Tunnels (P-tunnels) when selecting the upstream PE for a VPN multicast flow, and extending BGP MVPN routing so that a C-multicast route can be advertized toward a standby upstream PE.</description>
    <dc:date>2015-07-06T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
